"Sangkut" is a [[Singaporean]] slang used by local anglers and fishermen.  Occasionally some forms of spelling error my arise and it may be termed "Sangkok".

This is a malay term for snagging or entanglement.

In the context of fishing, its definition is "When one's terminal tackle is snagged on underwater debris or an underwater structure."
i.e. "darn, my lure has just got sangkut again.  Pass the lure retriever."


